https://www.googleapis.com/auth/doublecl.description: View and manage your reports in DoubleClick Bid Manager

description: API for viewing and managing your reports in DoubleClick Bid Manager.
name: doubleclickbidmanager

fields.description: Selector specifying which fields to include in a partial response.

key.description: API key. Your API key identifies your project and provides you with API access, quota, and reports. Required unless you provide an OAuth 2.0 token.

oauth_token.description: OAuth 2.0 token for the current user.

prettyPrint.description: Returns response with indentations and line breaks.

quotaUser.description: An opaque string that represents a user for quota purposes. Must not exceed 40 characters.

downloadlineitems.description: Retrieves line items in CSV format. TrueView line items are not supported.

uploadlineitems.description: Uploads line items in CSV format. TrueView line items are not supported.

deletequery.description: Deletes a stored query as well as the associated stored reports.

runquery.description: Runs a stored query to generate a report.

queryId.description: Query ID with which the reports are associated.

DownloadLineItemsRequest.description: Request to fetch stored line items.

fileSpec.description: File specification (column names, types, order) in which the line items will be returned. Default to EWF.

filterIds.description: Ids of the specified filter type used to filter line items to fetch. If omitted, all the line items will be returned.

filterType.description: Filter type used to filter line items to fetch.

format.description: Format in which the line items will be returned. Default to CSV.

lineItems.description: Retrieved line items in CSV format. For more information about file formats, see  Entity Write File Format.

DownloadRequest.description: Request to fetch stored inventory sources, campaigns, insertion orders, line items, TrueView ad groups and ads.

fileTypes.description:
File types that will be returned. If INVENTORY_SOURCE is requested, no other file types may be requested.

Acceptable values are:  
- "AD" 
- "AD_GROUP" 
- "CAMPAIGN" 
- "INSERTION_ORDER" 
- "INVENTORY_SOURCE" 
- "LINE_ITEM"

filterIds.description: The IDs of the specified filter type. This is used to filter entities to fetch. At least one ID must be specified.

filterType.description: Filter type used to filter entities to fetch. PARTNER_ID and INVENTORY_SOURCE_ID may only be used when downloading inventory sources.

version.description: SDF Version (column names, types, order) in which the entities will be returned. Default to 3.1.

adGroups.description: Retrieved ad groups in SDF format.

insertionOrders.description: Retrieved insertion orders in SDF format.

lineItems.description: Retrieved line items in SDF format.

FilterPair.description: Filter used to match traffic data in your report.

kind.description: Identifies what kind of resource this is. Value: the fixed string "doubleclickbidmanager#listQueriesResponse".
Identifies what kind of resource this is. Value: the fixed string "doubleclickbidmanager#listReportsResponse".

Parameters.description: Parameters of a query or report.

filters.description: Filters used to match traffic data in your report.

groupBys.description: Data is grouped by the filters listed in this field.

includeInviteData.description: Deprecated. This field is no longer in use.

metrics.description: Metrics to include as columns in your report.

kind.description: Identifies what kind of resource this is. Value: the fixed string "doubleclickbidmanager#query".

reportDataEndTimeMs.description: The ending time for the data that is shown in the report. Note, reportDataEndTimeMs is required if metadata.dataRange is CUSTOM_DATES and ignored otherwise.

reportDataStartTimeMs.description: The starting time for the data that is shown in the report. Note, reportDataStartTimeMs is required if metadata.dataRange is CUSTOM_DATES and ignored otherwise.

schedule.description: Information on how often and when to run a query.

timezoneCode.description: Canonical timezone code for report data time. Defaults to America/New_York.

googleCloudStoragePathForLatestReport.description: The path to the location in Google Cloud Storage where the latest report is stored.

googleDrivePathForLatestReport.description: The path in Google Drive for the latest report.

latestReportRunTimeMs.description: The time when the latest report started to run.

locale.description:
Locale of the generated reports. Valid values are cs CZECH de GERMAN en ENGLISH es SPANISH fr FRENCH it ITALIAN ja JAPANESE ko KOREAN pl POLISH pt-BR BRAZILIAN_PORTUGUESE ru RUSSIAN tr TURKISH uk UKRAINIAN zh-CN CHINA_CHINESE zh-TW TAIWAN_CHINESE

An locale string not in the list above will generate reports in English.

reportCount.description: Number of reports that have been generated for the query.

running.description: Whether the latest report is currently running.

sendNotification.description: Whether to send an email notification when a report is ready. Default to false.

shareEmailAddress.description: List of email addresses which are sent email notifications when the report is finished. Separate from sendNotification.

title.description: Query title. It is used to name the reports generated from this query.

QuerySchedule.description: Information on how frequently and when to run a query.

endTimeMs.description: Datetime to periodically run the query until.

frequency.description: How often the query is run.

nextRunMinuteOfDay.description: Time of day at which a new report will be generated, represented as minutes past midnight. Range is 0 to 1439. Only applies to scheduled reports.

nextRunTimezoneCode.description: Canonical timezone code for report generation time. Defaults to America/New_York.

key.description: Key used to identify a report.

ReportFailure.description: An explanation of a report failure.

errorCode.description: Error code that shows why the report was not created.

ReportKey.description: Key used to identify a report.

googleCloudStoragePath.description: The path to the location in Google Cloud Storage where the report is stored.

reportDataEndTimeMs.description: The ending time for the data that is shown in the report.

reportDataStartTimeMs.description: The starting time for the data that is shown in the report.

failure.description: If the report failed, this records the cause.

finishTimeMs.description: The time when this report either completed successfully or failed.

format.description: The file type of the report.

RowStatus.description: Represents the upload status of a row in the request.

changed.description: Whether the stored entity is changed as a result of upload.

errors.description: Reasons why the entity can't be uploaded.

RunQueryRequest.description: Request to run a stored query to generate a report.

dataRange.description: Report data range used to generate the report.

reportDataEndTimeMs.description: The ending time for the data that is shown in the report. Note, reportDataEndTimeMs is required if dataRange is CUSTOM_DATES and ignored otherwise.

reportDataStartTimeMs.description: The starting time for the data that is shown in the report. Note, reportDataStartTimeMs is required if dataRange is CUSTOM_DATES and ignored otherwise.

timezoneCode.description: Canonical timezone code for report data time. Defaults to America/New_York.

dryRun.description: Set to true to get upload status without actually persisting the line items.

format.description: Format the line items are in. Default to CSV.

lineItems.description: Line items in CSV to upload. Refer to  Entity Write File Format for more information on file format.

errors.description: Reasons why upload can't be completed.
